Eight Afghan police officers were
shot dead in an insurgent attack on their checkpoint last night
in southern Helmand province, an official said.  Authorities are searching for a policeman who escaped the
raid in the Nahr-e-Seraj district and is suspected to have aided
the guerrillas, Daud Ahmadi, spokesman for Helmandâ€™s government,
said in a phone interview. Three officers were injured.  To contact the reporter on this story:
